Class TypeElementTypePool

java.lang.Object
net.bytebuddy.pool.TypePool.AbstractBase
net.bytebuddy.pool.TypePool.AbstractBase.Hierarchical

org.microbean.clientproxy.bytebuddy.TypeElementTypePool
All Implemented Interfaces:
TypePool
public final class TypeElementTypePool extends TypePool.Default
A TypePool.Default that produces TypeDescriptions from javax.lang.model.* constructs.

Notably, this approach does not cause classloading to occur.

Author:
Laird Nelson

  • Method Details

    • describe

      public final TypePool.Resolution describe(String typePoolName)
      Given a name of an only partially defined format that names a Java language array, primitive, or declared type, or the void type, returns a TypePool.Resolution describing a TypeElementTypePool.TypeDescription corresponding to that name.

      The describe(String) method, which this one overrides only for documentation purposes, does not document what the supplied name must be beyond this:

      The name of the type to describe. The name is to be written as when calling Class.getName().

      We call names of this sort type pool names.

      Specified by:
      describe in interface TypePool
      Overrides:
      describe in class TypePool.AbstractBase.Hierarchical
      Parameters:
      typePoolName - a type pool name whose validity requirements are expressed only in source code; must not be null
      Returns:
      a non-null TypePool.Resolution
      Throws:
      NullPointerException - if typePoolName is null
